The paper discusses the joint control of inference and learnability, which is a topic commonly studied in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses data protection from inference attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of noise-free processes to alter joint distributions is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a new complexity measure, which is a topic commonly studied in information theory (cs.IT).
